# Windows Command Line Rules

## Directory Navigation
On Windows, always use:
```bash
# CORRECT
cd ../folder_name
cd C:/Users/Windows/path

# WRONG
cd ..\folder_name
cd C:\Users\Windows\path
```

## Path Separators in Commands
When running commands on Windows:
```bash
# CORRECT
docker run -v C:/Users/Windows/data:/data
python C:/path/to/script.py

# WRONG
docker run -v C:\Users\Windows\data:/data
python C:\path\to\script.py
```

## Current Working Directory
When running commands, check your location:
```bash
# Show current directory
pwd

# If in wrong directory, use absolute path
cd C:/Users/Windows/Documents/GitHub/carbon-backend

# Or relative path from current location
cd ../carbon-backend
```

## Docker Commands on Windows
Docker commands should use forward slashes:
```bash
# CORRECT
docker-compose -f ./docker-compose.yml up
docker run -v ./local:/container

# WRONG
docker-compose -f .\docker-compose.yml up
docker run -v .\local:/container
```

## Environment Variables
Setting environment variables on Windows cmd:
```bash
# CORRECT
set PATH=C:/path/to/bin;%PATH%

# WRONG
set PATH=C:\path\to\bin;%PATH%
```
